YWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzA3MjQmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1=
vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB12bc305a" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" item=
scope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decorat=
ion: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #00000=
0; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  a gold mine</a>. =
Eventually it sold all the common stock that its corporate charter allowed =
it to sell, and it couldn=E2=80=99t get its shareholders to approve more, b=
ecause meme-stock investors mostly don=E2=80=99t vote. So it created a new =
type of preferred stock, AMC Preferred Equity Units (APEs), and <a href=3D"=
https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32175659.262414/aHR0cHM6Ly93d=
3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDgtMjMvYW1jLWdvZXMtYXBl=
P2NtcGlkPUJCRDA3MjQyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1=
uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMDcyNCZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07c=
eef4b8524a319a23cB12dd9f36" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" =
target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important=
; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-sty=
le: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  gave out one APE</a> for every share =
of common stock. Then it sold more APEs to raise more money. Then it held a=
nother shareholder vote, in which the common shares and APEs voted together=
 as a single class, to approve (1) issuing new shares and (2) converting th=
e APEs into common stock. This vote was <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomb=
ergbusiness.com/click/32175659.262414/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vc=
GluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDItMDEvYW1jLWhhcy1zb21lLWNsZXZlci1hcGVzP2NtcGlk=
PUJCRDA3MjQyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV=
0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMDcyNCZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b852=
4a319a23cB8e5dedd5" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: so=
lid; background-color: #ccc;">  somewhat rigged</a> (the APEs would surely =
vote yes, and the voting mechanics basically turned=C2=A0<em>non-</em>votin=
g APEs into yes votes), and AMC <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusin=
ess.com/click/32175659.262414/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL=
2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDMtMTUvc2lsaWNvbi12YWxsZXktYmFuay1pcy1mb3Itc2FsZT9jbXBp=
ZD1CQkQwNzI0MjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2x=
ldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzA3MjQmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b85=
24a319a23cB564b790d" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: so=
lid; background-color: #ccc;">  won it</a>.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Before it could convert the APEs into common s=
tock, though, a class of common shareholders <a href=3D"https://link.mail.b=
loombergbusiness.com/click/32175659.262414/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNv=
bS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDItMjEvYW1jLWFwZXMtaGF0ZS1hbWMtcy1hcGVzP2N=
tcGlkPUJCRDA3MjQyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZX=
dzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMDcyNCZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef=
4b8524a319a23cB80cd9294" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" tar=
get=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; b=
order-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style:=
 solid; background-color: #ccc;">  sued</a>, claiming that this was all rig=
ged and illegitimate. AMC and the class eventually settled this lawsuit=C2=
=A0for <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32175659.26=
2414/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDQtMT=
AvZnR4LWxvc3QtdHJhY2stb2YtaXRzLW1vbmV5P2NtcGlkPUJCRDA3MjQyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJ=
nV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMDcyNCZ1=
dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB13b695a1" itemprop=
=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0=
00000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-b=
ottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">=
  a deal in which</a> (1) each APE would convert into one new common share =
but (2) each old common share would convert into about 1.13 new common shar=
es.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-1" style=3D"color: #000000=
; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom=
-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: tr=
ansparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[1]</span>
</a>=C2=A0The Delaware judge hearing the lawsuit, Vice Chancellor Morgan Zu=
rn, did not immediately sign off on the conversion: Some shareholders objec=
ted to the settlement, and she heard them out, commissioning a special mast=
er to examine the settlement. The special master <a href=3D"https://link.ma=
il.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32175659.262414/aHR0cHM6Ly9zMjUucTRjZG4uY29t=
LzQ3MjY0MzYwOC9maWxlcy9kb2NfZG93bmxvYWRzL3NoYXJlaG9sZGVyLW1lZXRpbmcvMjAyMy8=
wNi9SZXBvcnQtYW5kLVJlY29tbWVuZGF0aW9uLW9mLVNwZWNpYWwtTWFzdGVyLVJlZ2FyZGluZy=
1PYmplY3Rpb25zLXRvLVByb3Bvc2VkLVNldHRsZW1lbnQtd2l0aC1FeGhpYml0cy1hbmQtQXBwZ=
W5kaWNlcy5wZGY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB665fee54" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" it=
emscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decor=
ation: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000=
000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> filed a report</=
a> last month saying =E2=80=9Cmeh this seems fine.=E2=80=9D Many of the obj=
ections are meme-stock nonsense about dark pools, hedge funds, phantom shar=
es, naked shorts, etc.; I will not spend a lot of time on them, and neither=
 did the special master or Vice Chancellor Zurn.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But on Friday, Vice Chancellor Zurn <a href=3D=
"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32175659.262414/aHR0cHM6Ly93=
d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDctMjMvYW1jLXJldmlzZXMtc3R=
vY2stY29udmVyc2lvbi1zZXR0bGVtZW50LXBsYW4tcmVqZWN0ZWQtYnktanVkZ2U_Y21waWQ9Qk=
JEMDcyNDIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0Z=
XImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMwNzI0JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a31=
9a23cB1737e5a8" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_b=
lank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bot=
tom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; b=
ackground-color: #ccc;">  rejected the settlement</a>. Oops!</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Here is <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomberg=
business.com/click/32175659.262414/aHR0cHM6Ly9jb3VydHMuZGVsYXdhcmUuZ292L09w=
aW5pb25zL0Rvd25sb2FkLmFzcHg_aWQ9MzUwNDQw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB15b8b200"=
 itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"=
color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px;=
 border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color=
: #ccc;"> the opinion</a>. Her reason for rejection was fairly narrow and t=
echnical.=C2=A0The lawsuit was a class action on behalf of AMC=E2=80=99s co=
mmon shareholders, who claimed that AMC was treating them unfairly when it=
=C2=A0issued the APEs and tried to convert them=C2=A0into common stock. As =
in any class-action settlement, this one would release AMC from the class=
=E2=80=99s claims against it: The point of settling a class action is that =
no AMC shareholders can turn around and sue AMC=C2=A0<em>again=C2=A0</em>ov=
er this stuff. But the judge worried that the settlement released too=C2=A0=
<em>many=C2=A0</em>claims against AMC:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The release purports to release no=
t only claims associated with the common stock, but also claims associated =
with preferred interests that common stockholders might also hold. The rele=
ase cannot properly extend to those latter claims, because the plaintiffs w=
ere not appointed as fiduciaries for the holders of preferred interests and=
 did not bring claims based on preferred rights. The plaintiffs only sued o=
n behalf of a putative class of common stockholders, and only asserted clai=
ms based on the voting rights of common stockholders. They can agree to a r=
elease that encompasses the claims they asserted, and claims that the class=
 holds and that arise out of the same factual predicate.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">That is, the settlement would not only put to =
rest the complaints that AMC common shareholders might have about the APE d=
eal, but also any complaints that AMC=C2=A0<em>APEholders</em> might have.<=
/p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This makes no sense! The common shareholders h=
ad a complaint, they sued, and they negotiated a settlement in which they w=
ould get a somewhat better deal: They would get a bit more stock than the A=
PEholders, to make up for the somewhat fishy circumstances in which the APE=
holders got their APEs. But the APEholders hadn=E2=80=99t sued:=C2=A0<em>Th=
ey=C2=A0</em>had no complaints about the issuance of the APEs or their conv=
ersion into common stock; that was what they wanted. They were not involved=
 in the lawsuit, so no one speaks for them in the settlement.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And=C2=A0the=C2=A0<em>settlement </em>is=C2=A0=
<em>bad </em>for the APEholders: Instead of converting into common stock on=
 a one-for-one basis, they=E2=80=99re getting a bit less stock than the com=
mon shareholders. They bought APEs thinking that they would be economically=
 equivalent to AMC common stock, and now it turns out that they won=E2=80=
=99t be: The APEs are a little bit worse than common. The APEholders should=
 sue!</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">No they shouldn=E2=80=99t, not really: Convert=
ing into common, even at worse than a one-for-one ratio, really is what the=
y want. (On Friday, the APEs closed at $1.80 per share, while the common sh=
ares closed at $4.40: The common trades at a 144% premium to the APEs, vers=
us the 13% premium offered in the settlement.)=C2=A0Rationally the APEholde=
rs should like this deal.=C2=A0But since they are not involved in the lawsu=
it, the settlement can=E2=80=99t foreclose their claims. If they want to su=
e, they can go ahead.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Now, I am overstating it somewhat. The settlem=
ent wouldn=E2=80=99t release AMC from=C2=A0<em>all=C2=A0</em>APE claims. It=
 would release it from APE claims =E2=80=9Cthat common stockholders might h=
old=E2=80=9D: If you are an AMC common shareholder, you are part of this cl=
ass, and if you=C2=A0<em>also=C2=A0</em>own APEs then this settlement would=
 prevent you from suing AMC for treating your APEs unfairly. But if you own=
 only APEs and no common shares at all, then you are not part of the class =
and your claims are not released. But since a lot of people own both APEs a=
nd common shares (the APEs were originally distributed as a dividend on the=
 common), and in different proportions, it seems unfair to prevent a holder=
 of a million APEs from suing over their APE treatment=C2=A0if they happen =
to own one common share. =E2=80=9CAPE units are not represented in the comp=
laints or in the common stockholder class,=E2=80=9D writes Vice Chancellor =
Zurn, and so the lead plaintiffs of the class =E2=80=9Ccannot represent or =
release APE direct claims.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This seems right? Vice Chancellor Zurn raised =
it in court and everyone kind of ignored her; she writes:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I raised the fact that the Release=
 included APE claims released by common stockholders at argument to Plainti=
ffs and the defendants. Plaintiffs=E2=80=99 counsel first tried to describe=
 the APEs as a share split to color the APE claims as appurtenant to the co=
mmon shares, then deferred to the defendants=E2=80=99 counsel, and then won=
dered aloud if the defendants would drop that part of the Release. The defe=
ndants=E2=80=99 counsel simply insisted they were =E2=80=9Centitled to comp=
lete peace.=E2=80=9D</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anyway this seems obviously fixable:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">File a revised settlement releasing o=
nly the common claims, not the APE ones.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom:=
 5px;">Get that approved by the court.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5=
px;">
<em>Go ahead and convert the APEs into common</em>.</li>=09<li style=3D"mar=
gin-bottom: 5px;">If any APEholders want to sue, let them. Maybe they will =
win, and a court will give them some extra shares. Most likely they won=E2=
=80=99t, because this works out pretty well for them and they don=E2=80=99t=
 have a ton to complain about.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote=
-2" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-botto=
m-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !impo=
rtant; background-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[2]</span>
</a>
</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">AMC doesn=E2=80=99t get =E2=80=9Ccomplete peac=
e,=E2=80=9D but it gets to convert its APEs into common and then <em>sell m=
ore stock</em>, which is the main thing. AMC=E2=80=99s meme-y chief executi=
ve officer, Adam Aron, <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/c=
lick/32175659.262414/aHR0cHM6Ly90d2l0dGVyLmNvbS9DRU9BZGFtL3N0YXR1cy8xNjgzMj=
E1OTY1NjA4MTg5OTU0/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB15fe175d" itemprop=3D"StoryLink=
" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-d=
ecoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: =
#000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> tweeted an o=
pen letter</a> begging to be allowed to do that:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Raising fresh equity in the near term is criti=
cal to our company, so it is important that we work to address the concern =
raised in the Delaware Court of Chancery=E2=80=99s ruling on Friday. =E2=80=
=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">AMC must be in a position to raise equity capi=
tal. I repeat, to protect AMC=E2=80=99s shareholder value over the long ter=
m, we MUST be able to raise equity capital. =E2=80=A6=C2=A0If we are unable=
 to raise equity capital, the risk materially increases of AMC conceivably =
running out of cash in 2024 or 2025, or AMC being unable to satisfactorily =
refinance and stretch out the maturity of some of our debt. =E2=80=A6</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness=
.com/click/32175659.262414/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGlj=
bGVzLzIwMjMtMDctMjMvYW1jLXJldmlzZXMtc3RvY2stY29udmVyc2lvbi1zZXR0bGVtZW50LXB=
sYW4tcmVqZWN0ZWQtYnktanVkZ2U_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDcyNDIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZG=
l1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMwNzI0JnV0bV9jYW1wY=
