<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In October 2021, Trump Media &amp; Technology =
Group <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32175659.262=
414/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMTAtMjE=
vbWF0dC1sZXZpbmUtcy1tb25leS1zdHVmZi1kb25hbGQtdHJ1bXAtZG9lcy1hLXNwYWM_Y21waW=
Q9QkJEMDcyNDIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZ=
XR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMwNzI0JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b852=
4a319a23cB77ac2524" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: so=
lid; background-color: #ccc;"> announced</a> that it would go public by mer=
ging=C2=A0with Digital World Acquisition Corp., a special purpose acquisiti=
on company. This was certainly the first=C2=A0<em>I </em>had ever heard of =
Trump Media &amp; Technology Group, and I am pretty sure I am not alone. It=
 seemed, at the time, pretty half-baked. There were some plans for launchin=
g a social media site called Truth Social, but it did not exist yet. There =
was an investor presentation, but it was not replete with financial or busi=
ness information: I <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/clic=
k/32175659.262414/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzL=
zIwMjEtMTAtMjEvbWF0dC1sZXZpbmUtcy1tb25leS1zdHVmZi1kb25hbGQtdHJ1bXAtZG9lcy1h=
LXNwYWM_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDcyNDIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc29=
1cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMwNzI0JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/6=
07f07ceef4b8524a319a23cC77ac2524" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"items=
cope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !imp=
ortant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bott=
om-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> pointed out</a> that=C2=A0=E2=80=
=9Cthere is not a single dollar sign in the whole deck.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Digital World Acquisition Corp., meanwhile, wa=
s a SPAC that had gone public only a few weeks earlier. It had raised $287.=
5 million from investors, at $10 per share, to hunt for a company to take p=
ublic. =E2=80=9CWe intend to focus on middle market and emerging growth tec=
hnology-focused companies in the Americas, in SaaS and Technology or Fintec=
h and Financial Services,=E2=80=9D <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbu=
siness.com/click/32175659.262414/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZG=
dhci9kYXRhLzE4NDk2MzUvMDAwMTEwNDY1OTIxMTEzNTQxL3RtMjEyNzAzNWQxXzQyNGI0Lmh0b=
Q/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBb0aa201f" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"it=
emscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !=
important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-b=
ottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> it told prospective investors=
</a>. And: =E2=80=9CWe have not selected any specific business combination =
target and we have not, nor has anyone on our behalf, initiated any substan=
tive discussions, directly or indirectly, with any business combination tar=
get.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This was, <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombe=
rgbusiness.com/click/32175659.262414/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubnl0aW1lcy5jb20vMjAyMi=
8xMC8yNS9idXNpbmVzcy90cnVtcC1tZWRpYS1zcGFjLXNlYy5odG1s/607f07ceef4b8524a319=
a23cB03a52aaf" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_bl=
ank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; ba=
ckground-color: #ccc;"> it soon became apparent</a>, a lie. When DWAC filed=
 to go public, its sponsor was already in serious talks with Trump=E2=80=99=
s people to take TMTG public. DWAC was not really a blind pool of cash look=
ing for companies to take public; it was a vehicle specifically for taking =
TMTG public.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">You are not supposed to lie in securities fili=
ngs, so last week DWAC <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/c=
lick/32175659.262414/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9uZXdzL3ByZXNzLXJlbGVhc2UvMj=
AyMy0xMzU/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBe3bc373a" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemsco=
pe=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration=
: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; =
border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> agreed to pay $18 mil=
lion</a> to the US Securities and Exchange Commission, if the deal ever clo=
ses:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Securities and Exchange Commission [Thursd=
ay] announced=C2=A0settled fraud charges against Digital World Acquisition =
Corporation (DWAC), a special purpose acquisition company (SPAC), for makin=
g material misrepresentations in forms filed with the SEC as part of DWAC=
=E2=80=99s initial public offering and proposed merger with Trump Media &am=
p; Technology Group Corp. (TMTG). The Commission finds that DWAC misled inv=
estors and the SEC by failing to disclose that it had formulated a plan to =
acquire and was pursuing the acquisition of TMTG prior to DWAC=E2=80=99s IP=
O.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The purpose of a SPAC is to identify and acqui=
re an operating business. As such, steps taken by a SPAC in furtherance of =
a particular acquisition are important to investors. According to the SEC=
=E2=80=99s order, DWAC filed an amended Form S-1 in support of its IPO in e=
arly September 2021 that stated that neither DWAC nor its officers and dire=
ctors had had any discussions with any potential target companies prior to =
the IPO. But, as found in the SEC=E2=80=99s order, dating back to February =
2021, an individual who would later become DWAC=E2=80=99s CEO and Board Cha=
irman, and others involved with DWAC, had extensive SPAC merger discussions=
 with TMTG. The SEC=E2=80=99s order further finds that, while DWAC=E2=80=99=
s CEO and Chairman initially pursued these discussions with TMTG on behalf =
of another SPAC, he created a plan in the spring and summer of 2021 to pote=
ntially use DWAC to pursue a merger with TMTG and used this plan to solicit=
 certain pre-IPO investors. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CDWAC failed to disclose its discussio=
ns with TMTG and failed to disclose a material conflict of interest of its =
CEO and Chairman,=E2=80=9D=C2=A0said Gurbir S. Grewal, Director of the SEC=
=E2=80=99s Division of Enforcement. =E2=80=9CIn the context of a SPAC =E2=
=80=93 a =E2=80=98blank-check=E2=80=99 entity without business operations =
=E2=80=93 these disclosure failures are particularly problematic because in=
vestors focus on factors such as the SPAC=E2=80=99s management team and pot=
ential merger targets when making financial decisions.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">When we have <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloo=
mbergbusiness.com/click/32175659.262414/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9=
vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMTAtMjUvdGhlLXRydW1wLXNwYWMtaGFzLXNlYy10cm91Ym=
xlP2NtcGlkPUJCRDA3MjQyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZ=
T1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMDcyNCZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f0=
7ceef4b8524a319a23cB01534317" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope=
" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !importa=
nt; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-s=
tyle: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  discussed</a> this situation <a hre=
f=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32175659.262414/aHR0cHM6=
Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDYtMjkvdGhlLWJpZy1=
iYW5rcy1hcmVuLXQtc3RyZXNzZWQ_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDcyNDIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZG=
l1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMwNzI0JnV0bV9jYW1wY=
Wlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBdec10e6e" itemprop=3D"StoryLin=
k" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-=
decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color:=
 #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  previously=
</a>, I have pointed out that investors in DWAC were not really=C2=A0<em>ha=
rmed=C2=A0</em>by its lies.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-3"=
 style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-w=
idth: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !importa=
nt; background-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[3]</span>
</a>=C2=A0They bought DWAC stock at $10 in its public offering, thinking it=
 was a SPAC like any other, one that might or might not find an attractive =
deal. And then it quickly found the Trump deal and the stock shot up: The s=
tock closed at $9.96 the day before the Trump deal was announced, and $94.2=
0 two days later.=C2=A0If you bought DWAC stock for $10 in its initial publ=
ic offering, you were=C2=A0<em>deceived=C2=A0</em>about its plans, but in a=
=C2=A0<em>nice=C2=A0</em>way. You paid less for DWAC stock than it was wort=
h. That=E2=80=99s good!</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On the other hand =E2=80=A6=C2=A0why would DWA=
C do that? Why lie about its plans, in order to trick people into=C2=A0<em>=
underpaying=C2=A0</em>for the stock? I don=E2=80=99t know, but let me sugge=
st three possibilities.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One is just, like, sloppiness and incompetence=
? The standard form of SPAC prospectus says =E2=80=9Cwe have not had any su=
bstantive conversations with any target,=E2=80=9D so they just copied and p=
asted that even though it wasn=E2=80=99t true. Can=E2=80=99t really rule th=
at out.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Another=C2=A0is insider trading. You=C2=A0are =
an executive at DWAC, you want DWAC to=C2=A0sell stock to raise money, and =
you want it to be too cheap so that <em>you</em> can=C2=A0<em>buy=C2=A0</em=
>it cheaply, in the market, just before you announce the deal, and then you=
=C2=A0make money when you announce the deal and the stock pops. You want to=
 trick people into thinking the stock is worth less than it is, so you can =
make informed trades on the other side.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This explanation doesn=E2=80=99t make very muc=
h sense,<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-4" style=3D"color: #0=
00000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-b=
ottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-colo=
r: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[4]</span>
</a> and I mention it only because it =E2=80=A6=C2=A0appears to be true? We=
 <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32175659.262414/a=
HR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDYtMjkvdGhl=
LWJpZy1iYW5rcy1hcmVuLXQtc3RyZXNzZWQ_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDcyNDIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXR=
tX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMwNzI0JnV0bV=
9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cCdec10e6e" itemprop=3D"S=
toryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000=
; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom=
-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  tal=
ked last month</a> about a different <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomberg=
business.com/click/32175659.262414/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9uZXdzL3ByZXNz=
LXJlbGVhc2UvMjAyMy0xMjE/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB800561f8" itemprop=3D"Stor=
yLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; t=
ext-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-co=
lor: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> SEC enf=
orcement action</a> (and a related <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbu=
siness.com/click/32175659.262414/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuanVzdGljZS5nb3YvdXNhby1zZG=
55L3ByL3VzLWF0dG9ybmV5LWFubm91bmNlcy1jaGFyZ2VzLWZvdXItc2VwYXJhdGUtaW5zaWRlc=
i10cmFkaW5nLWNhc2VzLWFnYWluc3QtMTA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBc4295c96" itemp=
rop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color:=
 #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; borde=
r-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc=
;">federal criminal prosecution</a>), this one against a DWAC board member =
and his buddies, accusing them of insider trading by buying DWAC stock and =
warrants on the open market before the Trump deal was announced. So, sure, =
I guess.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But I think the real reason is that DWAC proba=
bly <em>couldn=E2=80=99t=C2=A0</em>have done this deal without lying. It=E2=
=80=99s not just that DWAC lied in its prospectus by saying it hadn=E2=80=
=99t had discussions with TMTG when it had. If it had told the truth =E2=80=
=94=C2=A0if it had said =E2=80=9Cwe=E2=80=99re a SPAC that=E2=80=99s raisin=
g money to take Trump Media &amp; Technology Group public=E2=80=9D =E2=80=
=94=C2=A0it wouldn=E2=80=99t have been allowed to do its offering in the fi=
rst place. A SPAC is supposed to be a blank-check company=C2=A0<em>without=
=C2=A0</em>any particular private company to take public. If you are raisin=
g money to take one particular company public, that=E2=80=99s not a SPAC. T=
hat=E2=80=99s just a regular initial public offering. You don=E2=80=99t jus=
t file for a blank check; you file for an initial public offering, with all=
 of the regular disclosure about the company=E2=80=99s business and finance=
s.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Could TMTG have done a regular initial public =
offering in October 2021? No? The investor presentation had no dollar signs=
. DWAC and TMTG eventually <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.c=
om/click/32175659.262414/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYX=
RhLzE4NDk2MzUvMDAwMTE5MzEyNTIyMTUwODAxL2QyMjYyMDVkczQuaHRt/607f07ceef4b8524=
a319a23cB29ec1b71" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D=
"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-=
bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid=
; background-color: #ccc;"> filed a prospectus</a> describing=C2=A0TMTG=E2=
=80=99s business, but it took them until May 2022. I=C2=A0<a href=3D"https:=
//link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32175659.262414/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmx=
vb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDUtMTYvdGhlLXRydW1wLXNwYWMtaX=
