 none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; b=
order-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  made fun of the prosp=
ectus=C2=A0at the time</a>, because it was still not all that businesslike,=
 and the stock is down about 60% since that filing. And the SEC has been ho=
lding up the deal ever since =E2=80=94=C2=A0in part, clearly, because of th=
e misstatements in DWAC=E2=80=99s original prospectus, but I suspect also a=
 little bit because they have their doubts about the business disclosure. I=
f TMTG had just filed for an initial public offering, I bet the SEC would h=
ave had lots of questions.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But meanwhile =E2=80=A6=C2=A0look, I do not us=
e Truth Social, but I gather that it exists, at least in some=C2=A0minimal =
sense of the word. The fact that TMTG was announced to the world along with=
 a $287.5=C2=A0million fundraising, a public listing, and a stock price tha=
t shot up 840% in two days was=C2=A0<em>useful=C2=A0</em>to TMTG. It attrac=
ted attention, and employees, and users, and hangers-on, and, not least, an=
other <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32175659.262=
414/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMTItMDY=
